Manchester United have stunned their supporters by signing Bolton Wanderers defender Andy Kellett on loan for the remainder of the season.

The 21-year-old has made just one appearance for Neil Lennon's side this season, playing 51 minutes in the Trotters' 4-2 defeat by Rotherham.

Kellett, who was on loan at Plymouth for three months earlier in the season, will join United's Under 21 side until June.

