He made his Bolton debut at the tail end of last season - playing in the final three games of the campaign - with a late substitute appearance in a 1-0 home defeat by Leicester. Further cameos followed in a 3-1 win at Sheffield Wednesday and a home draw with Birmingham.

It means Kellet has played 85 minutes of Championship football although he was a regular for Plymouth between October last year and January. He scored one goal - in a 3-2 win at Northampton - in 15 games, 

